+# Fix Summary: SharedFlow.toList(destination) Bug
+
+## Issue Description
+In kotlinx.coroutines version 1.7.0-Beta, the deprecated methods `SharedFlow.toList(destination)` and `SharedFlow.toSet(destination)` were not properly passing the `destination` parameter to the underlying Flow implementation. This caused the provided mutable collections to be ignored, making it impossible to collect SharedFlow emissions into a user-provided collection.
+
+## Root Cause
+In `/project/kotlinx-coroutines-core/common/src/flow/operators/Lint.kt`:
+
+**Before Fix:**
+```kotlin
+public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toList(destination: MutableList<T> = ArrayList()): List<T> =
+    (this as Flow<T>).toList()  // ❌ destination not passed!
+
+public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toSet(destination: MutableSet<T> = LinkedHashSet()): Set<T> =
+    (this as Flow<T>).toSet()   // ❌ destination not passed!
+```
+
+The functions accepted a `destination` parameter but didn't pass it to the underlying Flow methods, causing the parameter to be ignored.
+
+## Solution
+Modified `/project/kotlinx-coroutines-core/common/src/flow/operators/Lint.kt` to properly pass the destination parameter:
+
+**After Fix:**
+```kotlin
+public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toList(destination: MutableList<T> = ArrayList()): List<T> =
+    (this as Flow<T>).toList(destination)  // ✅ destination properly passed!
+
+public suspend inline fun <T> SharedFlow<T>.toSet(destination: MutableSet<T> = LinkedHashSet()): Set<T> =
+    (this as Flow<T>).toSet(destination)   // ✅ destination properly passed!
+```
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### Modified Files:
+1. `/project/kotlinx-coroutines-core/common/src/flow/operators/Lint.kt`
+   - Line 148: Added `destination` parameter to `toList()` call
+   - Line 160: Added `destination` parameter to `toSet()` call
+
+### New Test Files:
+1. `/project/kotlinx-coroutines-core/common/test/flow/SharedFlowToListTest.kt`
+   - Comprehensive tests for toList and toSet with SharedFlow
+   - Tests for pre-existing items preservation
+   - Tests for replay cache behavior
+
+2. `/project/kotlinx-coroutines-core/common/test/flow/SharedFlowToListBugTest.kt`
+   - Focused test reproducing the exact bug scenario from the issue report
+
+## Impact
+This fix restores the ability to use `SharedFlow.toList(mutableList)` and `SharedFlow.toSet(mutableSet)` for testing purposes (though these methods remain deprecated with a WARNING level because SharedFlow never completes).
+
+The typical use case now works correctly:
+```kotlin
+val acc = mutableListOf<Int>()
+val job = scope.launch(start = CoroutineStart.UNDISPATCHED) {
+    sharedFlow.toList(acc)
+}
+// ... emit values ...
+job.cancel()
+// acc now contains the emitted values ✅
+```
+
+## Testing
+Created comprehensive tests that verify:
+- Values collected from SharedFlow are properly added to the destination collection
+- Pre-existing items in the destination are preserved
+- Replay cache values are correctly collected
+- The exact bug scenario from the issue report is fixed
+

